<div id="form_container">
  <%= @Users.count %>
  <p>Welcome! Use the form below to generate notes about a user. Notes can include User attributes. Users have the following attributes:</p>
  <table>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>@first_name</td>
        <td>@last_name</td>
        <td>@phone_number</td>
        <td>@email</td>
        <td>@street_address</td>
        <td>@city</td>
        <td>@state</td>
        <td>@zip</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>For example: "Hi there @first_name @last_name! Is @phone_number still the best number to reach you?" will create a note reading: "Hi there Tadd Williams, Is (555) 555-5555 still the best number to reach you?"</p>

  <form>
    <fieldset>
      <legend>Create Note</legend>
      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <select>
          <option disabled selected> Select a User</option>
          <% @Users.each do |u|%>
          <option value="<% u.first_name %>"><%= u.first_name %></option>
          <% end %>
        </select>
      </div>
      <input type="text" name="firstname" placeholder="Hi there @first_name @last_name! Is @phone_number still the best number to reach you?"><br>
    </fieldset>
  </form>
</div>
